### What is Scope?

> Scope refers to the region in code where a variable is accessible.
> 
> 
> In Java, every variable exists only within a specific block â€” thatâ€™s its scope.
> 

---

### ðŸ”¹ What is Method Scope?

> A variable declared inside a method is called a local variable.
> 
> 
> It can only be accessed **within that method**.
> 

ðŸ“Œ When the method is called â†’ variable is created

ðŸ“Œ When the method ends â†’ variable is destroyed

