    static void greet() {
        String name = "Bablu";
        System.out.println("Hello, " + name); // âœ… Valid here
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        greet();
        // System.out.println(name); âŒ Error: 'name' not accessible here
    }
}
```

ðŸ” `name` is declared **inside `greet()`** â€” so it's only valid there.

